theorem closure_subset_closure_interior_closure_of_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A →
      closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
  intro hP1
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1
  -- Step 1 : `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)` by monotonicity of `closure`.
  have h₁ :
      closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (A : Set X)) :=
    closure_mono hP1
  -- Step 2 : `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`
  -- because `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)`.
  have h₂ :
      closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆
        closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
    apply closure_mono
    exact interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X))
  -- Combine the two inclusions.
  exact h₁.trans h₂
